it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface DataProperty.Equivalent<O,J,D extends DataProperty<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of DataProperty descriptor instantiated during buildEquivalentDataProperty() through getNewEquivalentDataProperty(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, DataProperty<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataPropertyExpression.Equivalent<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefinitionDataPropertyDesc, FullDataPropertyDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    DataProperty<O,J>

    public static interface DataProperty.Equivalent<O,J,D extends DataProperty<O,J>>
extends DataProperty<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a DataProperty to have the DataProperty.Equivalent expression.

      • buildEquivalentData

        default java.util.Set<D extends DataProperty<O,J>> buildEquivalentDataProperty

    • Method Detail

      • readExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildEquivalentDataProperty

        default java.util.Set<D> buildEquivalentDataProperty()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the disjointed data property of this property. Each of DataPropertys are instantiated through the method getNewEquivalentDataProperty(Object, Object); this is called for all getEquivalentDataProperties().

      • getNewEquivalentDataProperty

        D getNewEquivalentDataProperty(J instance,
                               O ontology)
        This method is called by buildEquivalentDataProperty() and its purpose is to instantiate a new DataProperty to represent an equivalent property of this DataProperty Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new equivalent DataProperty.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new DataProperty.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the equivalent properties of the one described by this interface.

      • synchroniseEquivalentDataPropertyToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseEquivalentDataPropertyToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with queryEquivalentDataProperties() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getEquivalentDataProperties(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the equivalent properties of Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); to the OWL representation.

      • synchroniseEquivalentDataPropertyFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseEquivalentDataPropertyFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls ExpressionEntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with queryEquivalentDataProperties() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getEquivalentDataProperties() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the equivalent data properties of Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance(); from an OWL representation to this Descriptor.
